<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id122a0ff5-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1331"><num value="1331">§ 1331.</num><heading> National Academy of Sciences: report</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to the usual number of the report of the National Academy of Sciences, two thousand copies shall be printed: five hundred for the Senate, one thousand for the House of Representatives, and five hundred for distribution by the National Academy of Sciences.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id122a0ff6-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1270">82 Stat. 1270</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id122a0ff7-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id122a0ff8-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 275 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s73">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 73</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/616">28 Stat. 616</ref>).</p>
</note>
